arm_group.description:
Patients diagnosed with either primary or secondary Takotsubo Syndrome.
TTS diagnosed based on modified Mayo Clinic Diagnostic Criteria as:
Transient wall motion abnormality in the left ventricle beyond a single epicardial coronary artery distribution;
Absence of obstructive coronary artery disease or angiographic evidence of acute plaque rupture, which can explain the wall motion abnormality;
New electrocardiographic abnormalities or elevation in cardiac troponin values;
Absence of pheochromocytoma or myocarditis.
